name: [oasis]
description:
"How many days have slipped by me, how many moments—disappearing, ignored by the morning star, cast aside viciously by the specter of time; the crucial realities that give life its meaning have been lost—I’m not sure what we’re doing any longer. I wake up in the morning, take chemicals into my bloodstream to ease the soreness and pain, use words to play out the riddles of mind and psyche—"

--Evan Retzer, The Daydream Society
